venue.name: Indian Institute of Information Technology and Management Gwalior

events.description:
Merry Christmas Folks!!!
Thank you for your enthusiasm and overwhelming response towards the GDG Gwalior Community. GDG Gwalior is all set to start its working and the Inauguration ceremony is going to take place on 4th Jan 2020 in ABV-IIITM Gwalior. The ceremony will focus on discussing the role of GDG and other opportunities for all you guys. See you next year!

events.name: Let's Talk Cloud!
events.description:
Google Cloudâ€™s server-less platform lets you write code your way without worrying about the underlying infrastructure. Come and join us and have a great learning... Also, Stay more productive and agile by using popular development languages and tools.

As this time GDG-GWALIOR community with two more Developer Communities - Women Techmakers and DSC RJIT is organizing a WEBINAR on Google Cloud.
Not only limited to GWALIOR but making it wider and wider this time.

Open for student as well as professional Developers who are in or thinking of making a decent career in the field of cloud computing!

Google Developer Expert Mr. Dharmesh Vaya is going to upskill the developers on Serverless Payment Architecture on GCP Hurry up and make yourself more eminent by registering yourself at: https://bit.ly/2wSDofr

Agenda for the event:
1. Intro to GCP cloud platform
2. Services it provides
3. How to use Google Pay API for app/ web development
4. Server-less Payment architecture of Google Pay
5. Hands on and QA session.

Note:
1. This event is free of cost.
2. Exciting prizes for most active participants.
3. Google Cloud certificate to every participant.

For more updates follow us on -
Instagram : https://www.instagram.com/invites/contact/?i=4e4zqyiw85d2&utm_content=b1663wn

events.name: Day-1 | Blockchain 101 on Tezos
events.description:
Are you getting bored and want to make effective use of this lockdown? If the answer is yes, then GDG Gwalior in partnership with Tezos has the perfect 2-day long Blockchain workshop for you.

Agenda for the workshop:
1. Intro to Tezos India Foundation
2. Intro to blockchain
3. The bitcoin story and Ethereum
4. Intro to Tezos
5. Tezos as a protocol
6. Running a Tezos node
7. Writing smart contract on Tezos
8. Intro to the Tezos development tools
9. Opportunities

All the participants will be rewarded from a certificate and the top 5 participants will receive a T-shirt from Tezos.
Note : All the participants are requested to go through the following resources to have a better grasp over the workshop.
1. https://hackernoon.com/wtf-is-the-blockchain-1da89ba19348
2. https://blockgeeks.com/guides/ethereum/
3. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=It96bIBPXZ0

Link:
Day 1: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9lHr-uVJtNI,
Day 2: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sBhuhDFUy5M
Date: 9 & 10 May, 2020
Time: 1:00 - 3:00 PM
